latestPosts.caption:
Tired of feeling “meh” in your clothes every summer?

✨ Chic girl summer (on a budget) ✨ is about looking chic, feeling confident, and actually wearing what’s in your wardrobe.

I’m building summer outfits with what I already own - using styling hacks, accessories, and a few intentional additions (not panic buys).

I’m saying no to hauls and summer identity meltdowns. Just minimal chic style that feels effortless and wearable.

Think:
✔ Outfit formulas you’ll come back to
✔ Jewellery & hair tweaks that change complete the look
✔ Style that works your life - not just your saves folder 

👉🏻 If you’re ready to feel confident getting dressed again, follow along & tap my profile for more chic summer on a budget inspiration. 🌞

latestPosts.caption:
PSA: outfit repeating is cool 🌞🌴🐚

~ swipe to the end for a stunning view ~

Outfit formula: maxi skirt, linen bandeau top, crochet bag & sandals = perfect summer outfit

This summer we’re rewearing our favourite pieces over and over again, you heard that right - we’re rewearing our favourite pieces because they deserve to be worn.

Maxi skirts are probably my favourite ‘summer’ wardrobe piece - they go with everything and just feel so effortless.

I’m a little obsessed with the starfish earrings & beaded jewellery. They are so fun. 

Are you team maxi skirt or mini skirt this summer? Vote below 🧡👇🏻
